                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 So 8/140: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Aden</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Park</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Aden</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-10-24T23:00:00+03:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 24, 1927—11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 25—2:39 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to Department’s telegram of October 17, 8 p.m. I have just received a
                    telegraphic communication from Ras Tafari stating that he is greatly pleased
                    that Mr. Southard whom he counts as a personal friend of long standing has been
                    selected to establish the new Legation at Addis Ababa,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Park</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
